criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  First-ever unilateral stroke;

          -  hemiplegia resulting from stroke;

          -  unilateral equinovarus gait with independent walk;

          -  able to ambulate without supporting devices.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  recurrent stroke;

          -  previous treatment with nerve blocks, motor point injections with neurolytic agents
             for spasticity at any time, or with BTX-A in the previous 6 months

          -  not independent in the basic activities of daily living

          -  severe cognitive deficits;

          -  progressive or severe neurologic diseases;

          -  fear to needles;

          -  any contraindication for dry needling, e.g., anticoagulants, infections, bleeding, or
             psychotic.
